summary: how to introduce gwen stacy in the mcu: a new student appears in midtown, gwen stacy. in this version, gwen looks like her...
body:
how to introduce gwen stacy in the mcu: a new student appears in midtown, gwen stacy. in this version, gwen looks like her counterpart in into the spiderverse, with shaved hair and piercings. at the same time, a white-hooded spider-powered vigilante who has been sabotaging oscorp’s laboratories. j. jonah jameson names her the ghost spider. at first, peter has an antagonistic relashionship with her. later in the movie, it’s revealed that gwen is the spider vigilante, with MJ acting as her ‘girl in the chair’. MJ already knows about peter’s identity and revealed it to gwen.

at the end of the movie, peter is pushed from the oscorp building by the main villain of the movie, the green goblin, and gwen saves him, like in the scene of the amazing spiderman 2.

for gwen i have three picks:

madison iseman

or

elle fanning

or

lana condor

(if there’s any spelling error, it’s because i’m brazilian)

summary:
Happy Halloween, Webheads! 🎃🍬

 

Back in 1987, people were worried that their Halloween candy was poisoned or had razor blades...
caption:
Happy Halloween, Webheads! 🎃🍬

Back in 1987, people were worried that their Halloween candy was poisoned or had razor blades or needles stuck in it. But luckily, Marvel had a solution — mini comic books instead! Heck, I’d take a Spider-Man comic over a Milky Way any day!

body:
Spideypool Halloween

PROMPT: It’s Tony Stark’s annual Avengers Halloween Party. This year’s theme is to dress up as your favorite hero, and (Thanks, Pep) you can’t dress up as yourself. Peter is obviously dressing up as Deadpool, and Wade is obviously dressing up as Spider-Man. It’s Wade’s first one so he’s excited to hang out with all the heroes and his spidey of course. Plus he’s really hoping that Cap will dress up as the Black Widow.

BUT Peter has other plans. Unbeknownst to Wade, Peter has used his charms to persuade all the Avengers (plus other heroes) to dress up as Deadpool as well. Because they haven’t been all that kind to him in the past and he still feels like he doesnt belong. But he does. And they eventually loved the idea.

So Wade and Peter (Spidey and Deadpool) walk in to a sea of Deadpools. Peter says, “Happy Halloween, Spidey.” In a soft loving voice.

Which Wade barely hears cuz he’s literally so stunned and so happy and no he isn’t crying. Shut up.

Someone write it.
